                            <comment id="103581" author="rwinch" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 09:14:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;NOTE I&apos;m going to see if I can get this done by 3.2.4, but it is going to be tight. It may require waiting until 3.2.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="103896" author="marekw" created="Wed, 28 May 2014 05:52:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that this issue has the following consequences:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Internal methods calls (this.someMethod(...)) will not be intercepted by JDK proxies, thus ignoring some authorization checks when JavaConfig is used instead of XML&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;JDK proxies may not be exported as MBeans by Spring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="106294" author="rwinch" created="Fri, 25 Jul 2014 14:08:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is now resolved. You can also find a sample demonstrating the usage of method security and AspectJ at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/tree/b2d66e2a78b3f94e574d82dbe208ac7451223481/samples/aspectj-jc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/tree/b2d66e2a78b3f94e574d82dbe208ac7451223481/samples/aspectj-jc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
